Assisted by ornithologists from the Dnepropetrovsk National University, who developed a scheme for the transfer of nests.
They also conducted trainings for the staff of the regional networks.
The well-known Dnepropetrovsk ornithologist Alexander Ponomarenko consulted energy scientists at all stages of the reconstruction of the nest.
To begin with, it was estimated that there are more than 50 authentic "apartments" in the area in the state of emergency.
For their reconstruction, special metal platforms resembling a funnel were welded.
The base was flooded with oak branches, and then transferred to the old nest.
According to the connoisseurs, it is enough to lay the old branches as the basis for the birds to recognize the nest and return to it.
After that, the residents will build their own homes.
A month ago, the first nest was reconstructed in the village of Peschanka Novomoskovsky district.
Next to the electric pole they put a new reinforced concrete pole and placed on it a platform with an old, already swollen nest.
The entire operation cost the energy workers 9,000 hryvnias.
And the other day the same novice took place in the village of Ivanovka Petrikovsky district in the courtyard of grandmother Ani.
Here the platform was fixed in the previous place, only raised above the wires.
Ornithologists are sure that cautious, conservative birds won’t even notice in the spring that their “apartment” will be subject to capital repairs.
Until the end of the year, the same reconstruction expects four more nests in the Pokrovsky and Tsarychinsky districts of Dnepropetrovsk.
