Recall that three years ago, on December 11, a natural meeting of nationalists took place on Manezhnaya Square, which grew into mass riots.
Levada Center also asked the Russians what holiday is celebrated on November 4th.
In two years, the number of those who know the right answer (Day of People’s Unity) has increased from 41% to 49%.
