According to The New York Times, President Barack Obama’s closest advisers secretly considered the possibility of replacing Vice President Joe Biden with Hillary Clinton’s nomination in the 2012 electoral roll.
This discovery is the most vivid sensation of all the expected books by Mark Galperin and John Haylemann about the 2012 campaign "Stats Doubled: The Game Changed 2012".
The Times received a copy of the book ready for release and reported Thursday evening that the president’s closest aides conducted “large-scale research in focus groups and public opinion polls at the end of 2011” to assess whether Biden’s re-election exception could help lift the bill.
