The possible replacement was a secret, carefully guarded in the Chicago Pre-Election Office and in the Oval Office.
Only six of the president’s closest advisers — including Daley, former chief of Obama’s pre-election staff Jim Messina and former senior White House advisers David Axelrod and David Plumf — knew the replacement was under consideration.
