In an interview with Martin Daley, he confirmed that the administration had indeed considered the possibility of replacing Biden Clinton.
“I was actively speaking for the consideration of a lot of things, and that was one of them,” Daley told the newspaper.
You have to remember that at the time the president was in terrible shape, so we thought, “Oh my God, what should we do?”
