“The pre-election headquarters don’t spend that much money on surveys and focus groups unless they’re looking at something seriously,” Martin said in the AK 360 program.
It is unclear, however, if Obama knew that his team was studying the possibility of a replacement.
Martin told CNN that he had asked Daley if his then-boss knew about a possible transfer.
Although Daley said he didn’t think the president “was aware” of a possible replacement, the former head of the administration admitted that “possibly” Obama knew.
Martin added that the “doubled stakes” did not give a clear answer to the question of whether the results of the political probe had come to Obama’s table.
Cooper asked Martin if he seriously thought Obama didn’t know about the study of the possibility of excluding Biden from the electoral list.
“Perhaps,” Martin replied.
