Cooperation with other single-member countries will be easier in non-federal Europe of nations.
Otherwise, we should consider the possibility of repeating Norway’s experience and maintaining our economic independence.
The Scottish National Party’s government in Scotland is, oddly enough, the most successful political movement in Europe, aimed at countering austerity measures, which received an impressive majority of votes in 2011 due to objections to the reduction in the costs proposed (and implemented) by the Abortion Commission.
